DISCRIPTION: The Automatic Sanitizer Dispenser uses an IR sensor to detect a hand placed near the nozzle.
When a hand is detected, the Arduino activates a DC pump or servo motor to dispense sanitizer automatically â€” ensuring touch-free and hygienic operation.
CODING:
int sensor = 2;      // IR sensor pin
int pump = 3;        // Motor or pump pin

void setup() {
  pinMode(sensor, INPUT);
  pinMode(pump, OUTPUT);
}

void loop() {
  int detect = digitalRead(sensor);
  if (detect == LOW) {         // Hand detected
    digitalWrite(pump, HIGH);  // Turn ON pump
    delay(1000);               // Dispense for 1 sec
    digitalWrite(pump, LOW);   // Turn OFF pump
  } else {
    digitalWrite(pump, LOW);
  }
}
